<body>
  <%- include('../partials/navbar') %>

  <main id="main-content" class="container page-main project-management-page">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Project Management &amp; Delivery</h1>

      <p class="lead">
        Project management experience connecting planning, team coordination, requirements, testing, and software delivery.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="text-section">
      <h2>Project management in software delivery</h2>

      <p>
        My project experience includes coordinating team work, planning delivery around milestones and sprint goals,
        supporting communication, and connecting requirements with implementation and testing. This page summarises the
        project management responsibilities I have taken across software, accessibility, and game development projects.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="text-section">
      <h2>Role evidence</h2>

      <div class="table-responsive project-management-table-wrap">
        <table class="project-management-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Project management role</th>
              <th scope="col">Example from existing projects</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Planning and delivery coordination</strong></td>
              <td>
                Planned and coordinated team delivery across university software projects, including sprint-based work,
                MVP goals, documentation, and final submission requirements. Evidence includes the
                <a class="text-link" href="/projects/audio-track-chat-app">Audio Track Chat App</a>
                and the
                <a class="text-link" href="/projects/oagp">Online Accessibility Governance Platform</a>.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td><strong>Team communication and responsibility tracking</strong></td>
              <td>
                Supported role clarity, progress updates, task allocation, and communication across team members. This
                was central to my Project Manager work on the
                <a class="text-link" href="/projects/audio-track-chat-app">Audio Track Chat App</a>
                and my delivery contribution to
                <a class="text-link" href="/projects/oagp">OAGP</a>.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td><strong>Requirements and quality alignment</strong></td>
              <td>
                Connected project goals, functional expectations, accessibility needs, and testing evidence so delivery
                stayed aligned with the intended outcome. This is reflected in the
                <a class="text-link" href="/projects/oagp">Online Accessibility Governance Platform</a>
                and testing-focused university project work.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td><strong>Testing within the project lifecycle</strong></td>
              <td>
                Treated testing as part of delivery rather than a separate final step. In the
                <a class="text-link" href="/projects/audio-track-chat-app">Audio Track Chat App</a>,
                I wrote the automated JUnit 5 and Mockito test suite and created the k6 load testing script.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td><strong>Technical leadership</strong></td>
              <td>
                Led programming work by translating project goals into playable systems, interaction logic, and
                technical implementation in the
                <a class="text-link" href="/projects/wisdom-game">Wisdom Game Project</a>.
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

